
A total of 108 ships are to berth in Lagos ports in October.

The shipping position released by the Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA) in Lagos on
Friday showed that many of the ships will be carrying containers, vehicles and
petroleum products.

The shipping position showed that 15 of the ships, laden with different
petroleum products, mostly petrol, are already waiting for clearance to berth.

Eighteen other ships are carrying bulk cargoes like fish, fertilizer, bulk
cement, bulk urea, bulk salt and containers.

Meanwhile, the Nigerian Port Authority (NPA) has issued a statement assuring
stakeholders that there would no longer be congestion at any of the nation's
ports.

NPA said it was now committed to efficient port operations.
